        "published": "2025-07-18",
        "description": "A certificate verification error in wolfSSL when building with the WOLFSSL_SYS_CA_CERTS and WOLFSSL_APPLE_NATIVE_CERT_VALIDATION options results in the wolfSSL\n client failing to properly verify the server certificate's domain name,\n allowing any certificate issued by a trusted CA to be accepted regardless of the hostname.",
        "title": "A certificate verification error in wolfSSL when building with the WOLFSSL_SYS_CA_CERTS and WOLFSSL_APPLE_NATIVE_CERT_VALIDATION options...",
        "cvss_max": 9.2
      },
      "cve": {
        "id": "CVE-2025-7395",
        "sourceIdentifier": "facts@wolfssl.com",
        "published": "2025-07-18T23:15:23.657",
        "lastModified": "2026-04-15T00:35:42.020",
        "vulnStatus": "Deferred",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "A certificate verification error in wolfSSL when building with the WOLFSSL_SYS_CA_CERTS and WOLFSSL_APPLE_NATIVE_CERT_VALIDATION options results in the wolfSSL\n client failing to properly verify the server certificate's domain name,\n allowing any certificate issued by a trusted CA to be accepted regardless of the hostname."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "Un error de verificación de certificado en wolfSSL al compilar con las opciones WOLFSSL_SYS_CA_CERTS y WOLFSSL_APPLE_NATIVE_CERT_VALIDATION da como resultado que el cliente wolfSSL no verifique correctamente el nombre de dominio del certificado del servidor, lo que permite que se acepte cualquier certificado emitido por una CA confiable independientemente del nombre de host."
          }
        ],
